===Future and planned September 11 memorials===
* Palm Harbor 9/11 Memorial, [[Palm Harbor, Florida]] <U+2013> This memorial broke ground {{As of|2012|3|30|alt=on March 30, 2012}}. It will be designed around a 150-pound piece of World Trade Center steel provided (and still owned) by the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey.<ref>{{cite web|last=Horchy|first=Eric|title=Groundbreaking for planned Palm Harbor 9/11 Memorial|url=http://suncoastpinellas.tbo.com/content/2012/mar/22/PINEWSO3-groundbreaking-for-planned-palm-harbor-91/news/|work=The Suncoast News|accessdate=March 22, 2012}}</ref>
* Huntington Beach 9/11 Memorial, [[Huntington Beach, California]] <U+2013> A design plan has been selected for this Memorial which is currently in the fundraising stage.  The Memorial will be built outside the Huntington Beach City Hall building and will be dedicated on September 11, 2013.  The Memorial design features two stainless steel towers and will incorporate two girders from the New York World Trade Center  provided by the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey.  The words <U+201C>We Will Never Forget<U+201D> will be etched along the base of the memorial.<ref>{{cite web|last=Katapodis|first=Jim|title=Huntington Beach 9/11 Memorial|url=http://www.jimkatapodis.com/archives/huntington-beach-911-memorial/}}</ref>

